WEBVTT

00:28.070 --> 00:33.908
[ Train Whistle Blows ]

00:34.702 --> 00:36.244
[ Bell Jingles ]

00:51.385 --> 00:54.137
[ Man ]
I don't know a recent Saturday I've sold more.

00:55.055 --> 00:57.682
[ Engine Starts ]

00:57.766 --> 00:59.559
Why are you so glum?

00:59.643 --> 01:02.520
Were you bothered
by those waitresses making a fuss?

01:02.604 --> 01:04.730
No.

01:04.815 --> 01:08.067
But, honest, what are you supposed to do
when people keep commenting on your looks?

01:08.152 --> 01:11.362
I don't even know what they mean -
"Beat 'em off with a stick."

01:11.447 --> 01:14.490
[ Chuckles ]
Well, if that's your only problem -

01:14.575 --> 01:16.325
It's not.

01:18.829 --> 01:20.371
I got my report card.

01:23.333 --> 01:25.626
Three C's, two D's...

01:25.711 --> 01:27.503
and an incomplete.

01:28.839 --> 01:32.008
I see you studying so hard, Tom.

01:32.092 --> 01:33.885
What do you think the problem is?

01:33.969 --> 01:36.220
I just have to try harder.

01:37.848 --> 01:41.100
I will.

01:41.185 --> 01:42.894
I will. I will.

01:42.978 --> 01:44.729
I will! I will

01:44.813 --> 01:46.522
I will, I will, I will. I will!

01:48.192 --> 01:50.151
[ Exhales ]

01:51.528 --> 01:53.988
[ Chuckles ]
Thanks, Dad. This talk helped.

01:55.073 --> 01:56.574
Can you, um...

01:56.658 --> 01:58.701
sign it, please?

02:06.251 --> 02:09.044
Do you think it would help
if I got you a tutor?

02:10.672 --> 02:13.299
That'd be great.

02:13.383 --> 02:17.595
It'd better help though. What can you do
with yourself if all you can do is look good?

02:22.434 --> 02:25.478
I'm frequently asked
what special difficulties are involved...

02:25.562 --> 02:29.482
in being graduated from high school
two months shy of my 15th birthday.

02:29.566 --> 02:34.111
I sometimes think it was the difficulties themselves
which enabled me to do it.

02:34.196 --> 02:37.573
If I'd been appreciated,
or even tolerated...

02:37.658 --> 02:39.867
I wouldn't have been
in such a hurry to graduate.

02:40.828 --> 02:44.038
And I hope the next student
who comes along and is able to excel...

02:44.122 --> 02:47.500
isn't made to feel so much an outcast.

02:47.584 --> 02:49.669
But I'm looking forward to college...

02:49.753 --> 02:54.507
and this is the happiest day I've had
in a long, long time.

02:54.591 --> 02:56.592
So, I thank you...

02:56.677 --> 02:59.136
and I forgive you.

02:59.221 --> 03:01.889
- [ Boys Shouting ]
- [ Boy ] Slug him. Slug him!

03:01.974 --> 03:05.518
- [ Crowd Reacting ]
- Go ahead, Steven. Take your last licks.

03:05.602 --> 03:09.522
But this will heal!
What I'm gonna say can never be erased!

03:09.606 --> 03:11.148
It'll scar you forever!

03:11.233 --> 03:13.401
Ready? Here it is.

03:13.485 --> 03:17.738
You'll never make more than $19,000 a year!
Ha, ha, ha!

03:17.823 --> 03:19.490
- [ Crowd Shouting ]
- [ Boy ] Cream him!

03:19.575 --> 03:21.325
Take him.

03:29.751 --> 03:31.919
Okay! What about this?

03:32.004 --> 03:36.549
You'll never leave South Boston,
and I'm gonna see the whole damn world!

03:36.633 --> 03:39.719
You'll never know the pleasure
of writing a graceful sentence...

03:39.803 --> 03:41.637
or having an original thought!

03:41.722 --> 03:43.806
Think about it.

03:43.891 --> 03:46.893
$19,000 - not bad.

03:46.977 --> 03:49.145
[ School Bell Rings ]

03:50.230 --> 03:53.941
Dear Felicio,
It's truly amazing to me...

03:55.277 --> 03:59.780
that we live a world apart
and yet have the same favorite music.

03:59.865 --> 04:02.033
I love the picture you sent me...

04:02.117 --> 04:04.410
and have it up on -
Oops.

04:04.494 --> 04:06.412
And have it -

04:06.496 --> 04:09.123
And have it up on my bulletin board.
The drawing -

04:09.207 --> 04:10.708
- Honey.
- [ Screams ]

04:10.792 --> 04:13.419
Good God, Jane!

04:13.503 --> 04:16.339
Daddy! Don't ever do that to me!

04:17.048 --> 04:19.382
Look, It's time for you to go to sleep.

04:19.468 --> 04:22.053
I just have two more pen pals.
Then I'm all done.

04:22.763 --> 04:26.974
[ Sighs ] Finish quickly. I don't want you
getting obsessive about these things.

04:27.059 --> 04:28.851
- Good night.
- Good night.

04:29.978 --> 04:32.021
All right.

04:32.105 --> 04:33.773
"Obsessive."

04:35.108 --> 04:37.234
"Obsessive."
[ Gasps ]

04:38.195 --> 04:43.282
Dad, you want me
to choose my words so carefully.

04:43.367 --> 04:45.534
Then you throw a word
like "obsessive" at me.

04:45.619 --> 04:48.913
Now, unless I'm wrong -
please correct me if I am -

04:48.997 --> 04:51.958
but obsession is practically
a psychiatric term...

04:52.042 --> 04:54.043
concerning people
who don't have anything else...

04:54.127 --> 04:56.253
but the object of their own obsession...

04:56.338 --> 04:58.589
who can't stop and do anything else.

04:58.674 --> 05:02.510
Well, here I am stopping
to tell you this, okay?

05:02.594 --> 05:05.221
So would you please try
and be a little bit more precise...

05:05.305 --> 05:08.683
instead of calling a person
something like "obsessive"?

05:11.311 --> 05:12.937
- [ Kisses ]
- Good night.

06:03.613 --> 06:05.114
Hey, it's me.

06:05.198 --> 06:07.867
Um, it's 30 minutes before
you have to meet me in the lobby.

06:07.951 --> 06:11.078
Nudge your mate.
Uh, I don't think there's time to eat...

06:11.163 --> 06:14.915
but there's probably a cafeteria
at the bus depot once we get down there.

06:15.000 --> 06:18.252
I love working with you two.
It saves me a call.

06:18.879 --> 06:20.004
Yeah.

06:22.924 --> 06:24.967
[ Line Ringing ]

06:25.052 --> 06:26.052
- [ Man ] Hi.
- Hey.

06:26.136 --> 06:27.762
Gotta turn on your television right now.

06:27.846 --> 06:31.223
Arnold Schwarzenegger is on The Today Show,
Good Morning, America and The Morning News.

06:31.308 --> 06:33.768
- I think he's live on two of them.
- [ Chuckling ]

06:33.852 --> 06:36.896
At 6:00 on The Wake-up News
they used the wrong missile graphic.

06:36.980 --> 06:41.025
And they called me this morning to say they want
us to take even cheaper rooms on the road now.

06:41.109 --> 06:42.985
[ Imitating Schwarzenegger ]
Now, listen. Arnold just said he's making...

06:43.070 --> 06:46.614
$3 million a movie now,
but he's not ever gonna change.

06:46.698 --> 06:50.451
He's still the same person
when he was making $2 million a movie.

06:50.535 --> 06:52.036
He feels no different.

06:52.120 --> 06:55.581
He also bought a brand-new condo with Maria
they're gonna furnish tastefully.

06:55.665 --> 06:57.792
[ Chuckling ]

06:57.876 --> 06:59.376
Half hour in the lobby.

06:59.461 --> 07:01.295
Okay. I'll see you in the lobbies.

07:32.035 --> 07:35.079
[ Sobbing ]

07:56.810 --> 07:59.728
[ Sighs, Gasps ]

08:15.787 --> 08:20.833
There he is.
Hi. I'd like to talk to you for a second.

08:23.253 --> 08:25.212
- Just a few questions.
- No.

08:25.297 --> 08:28.215
- Well, I came all the way from Washington.
- Move away from me.

08:28.300 --> 08:30.968
[ Jane ]
"There might be a band and bunting...

08:31.052 --> 08:34.013
um, at the bus depot
for J.D. Singer's return from war.

08:34.139 --> 08:38.183
- Last week, he was decorated
by a president for heroism in the war" -
- No, watch this.

08:38.268 --> 08:40.019
I want you to watch this.
You weren't there for it. Watch.

08:40.102 --> 08:44.273
- How does it feel being home?
- Get the fuck - Fuck. Fuck.

08:44.357 --> 08:47.151
- [ Laughing ]
- Fucking! Snot! Fucking!

08:47.235 --> 08:50.738
- You want to use that?
- Depends on how big a news day it is.

08:51.364 --> 08:54.533
- Thanks.
- I can't believe you said that!

08:54.618 --> 08:58.287
- I'm very proud of that.
- He really opened up to you, man.

08:58.371 --> 09:01.874
If this were a war that was sanctioned
by the United States -

09:01.958 --> 09:04.084
if it were Korea or World War II
or Vietnam...

09:04.169 --> 09:07.087
- then obviously coming back
would have a different-
- 40-10.

09:07.172 --> 09:08.839
You really oughta work
on your speech.

09:08.924 --> 09:10.633
Oh, no.

09:10.717 --> 09:12.301
[ Sighs ]

09:12.385 --> 09:15.554
It makes me nervous to think about it.
Let's do this.

09:15.639 --> 09:17.598
[ Man ]
I'm not expecting any big homecoming.

09:19.309 --> 09:21.185
We are being increasingly influenced...

09:21.269 --> 09:23.187
by the star system.

09:23.271 --> 09:27.650
The network anchormen are so powerful
they comprise our last best hope.

09:28.818 --> 09:32.655
- Our profession is in danger.
- [ Clears Throat ]

09:32.739 --> 09:34.907
- [ Crowd Murmuring ]
- [ Woman ] So, where do you want to go eat?

09:34.991 --> 09:39.662
The current group is clearly qualified,
tied still to our best traditions.

09:39.746 --> 09:45.334
- But who follows these men?
- [ Man Sighs ] Excuse me.

09:45.418 --> 09:47.586
- [ Man Groans ]
- We are being pressured...

09:47.671 --> 09:50.756
- to take a loyalty oath -
- Wow.

09:50.840 --> 09:53.133
Oh, I've known so many women like that.

09:53.218 --> 09:55.886
They don't like their looks,
so they're angry.

09:55.971 --> 09:57.846
[ Woman ]
Excuse me.

10:03.186 --> 10:04.937
All of you know what I'm talking about.

10:05.021 --> 10:08.607
We're - We're all trying to act
tougher than we are.

10:08.692 --> 10:09.858
But we care.

10:09.943 --> 10:12.319
So...

10:12.404 --> 10:16.323
we're all secretly terrified
by what's happening, aren't we?

10:18.076 --> 10:19.076
[ Man Sneezes ]

10:19.160 --> 10:22.329
[ Woman Giggling ]

10:25.333 --> 10:26.792
[ Man ]
Catch you later.

10:26.876 --> 10:29.503
I was gonna talk
about other trends, but -

10:30.380 --> 10:32.798
"Magazine shows, news as profit...

10:32.882 --> 10:36.635
the historic influence
of Entertainment Tonight...

10:36.720 --> 10:38.220
the danger, the hope...

10:38.305 --> 10:40.306
the dream, the question."

10:40.390 --> 10:42.016
Oh!

10:42.100 --> 10:43.726
I was gonna show you a tape...

10:43.810 --> 10:48.731
a story carried by all networks
on the same night - the same night -

10:48.815 --> 10:52.693
that not one network noted
a major policy change...

10:52.777 --> 10:55.362
in Salt II nuclear disarmament talks.

10:55.447 --> 10:58.032
Here's what they ran instead.

10:58.116 --> 10:59.950
Go ahead. Please show the tape.

11:00.035 --> 11:03.454
[ All Speaking Foreign Language On Screen ]

11:23.016 --> 11:27.102
I know it's good film.
I know it's fun. I like fun.

11:28.897 --> 11:30.814
- It's just not news.
- [ Explosion On Screen ]

11:38.239 --> 11:42.076
Well, you're lucky you love it.
You're gonna get a lot more just like it.

11:43.203 --> 11:44.328
[ Woman ]
Good.

11:51.211 --> 11:52.419
Thank you.

12:05.016 --> 12:06.975
I don't think there'll be any Q and A.

12:13.233 --> 12:16.235
[ Chattering ]

12:29.416 --> 12:30.916
[ Man ]
Hi.

12:32.085 --> 12:33.585
[ Jane ]
Hello.

12:43.012 --> 12:45.848
I just wanted to tell you
how great you were.

12:46.975 --> 12:48.684
My name's Tom Grunick.

12:53.815 --> 12:55.357
Thank you.

12:55.442 --> 12:56.817
Yeah.

13:07.954 --> 13:09.746
They hated me.

13:11.541 --> 13:13.542
I don't hate them.

13:13.626 --> 13:16.503
Well, they say if you can reach even one person,
it means something.

13:18.548 --> 13:21.049
[ Clicks Teeth ]
And you did that.

13:23.470 --> 13:27.014
- Would you like to have dinner with me?
- [ Chuckles ]

13:28.975 --> 13:30.225
Sure.

13:32.061 --> 13:35.063
You know what I'm saying?
Another thing I can't stand -

13:35.148 --> 13:39.443
- Is this dull?
- No! No. No. No. No.

13:39.527 --> 13:44.698
Another thing I can't stand is when White House
reporters bullshit with each other after a briefing...

13:44.782 --> 13:47.034
and then one of them has a theory...

13:47.118 --> 13:52.164
and the other quotes it in his story as,
"White House sources say" -

13:52.248 --> 13:54.833
- That actually goes on?
- Yes.

13:54.918 --> 13:58.295
I am not tired. My room is right down here.
You want to keep talking?

13:58.379 --> 14:00.589
Yeah, sure.

14:05.136 --> 14:06.762
Oh, come on.

14:08.431 --> 14:10.849
Even I'm not that hard on myself.

14:10.934 --> 14:12.518
No, really.

14:13.978 --> 14:16.438
I got this job on a fluke.

14:17.106 --> 14:19.316
And wait till you hear how it ends up.

14:19.984 --> 14:21.485
[ Clears Throat ]

14:21.569 --> 14:24.112
I was doing sports at this station.

14:25.281 --> 14:28.408
The newspaper ran this untrue story...

14:28.493 --> 14:30.577
that I was leaving...

14:30.662 --> 14:33.622
and they got these tons of protest mail.

14:33.706 --> 14:35.290
- [ Laughing ]
- So -

14:37.502 --> 14:39.002
So they made me anchor.

14:40.129 --> 14:41.672
So, great. Right?

14:41.756 --> 14:46.260
Except I'm no good
at what I'm being a success at.

14:46.928 --> 14:49.638
How are you at back rubs?
[ Growls ]

15:06.155 --> 15:08.699
It's sort of normal,
the way you feel.

15:08.783 --> 15:11.159
In graduate school,
everyone thought the only mistake...

15:11.244 --> 15:12.953
the admissions committee made
was letting 'em in.

15:13.037 --> 15:16.498
Listen to me.
You keep thinking I'm somebody who -

15:16.583 --> 15:18.208
[ Sighs ]
who lacks confidence.

15:18.293 --> 15:20.419
That's not it. I know.
I can talk well enough...

15:20.503 --> 15:22.296
and I'm not bad at making
contact with people.

15:22.380 --> 15:26.592
But I don't like the feeling
that I'm pretending to be a reporter.

15:26.676 --> 15:30.512
And half the time,
I don't get the under -

15:30.597 --> 15:32.180
the news that I'm talking about.

15:33.182 --> 15:36.602
[ Scoffs ]
It's not that I'm down on myself. Trust me.

15:37.395 --> 15:39.688
I stink!

15:39.772 --> 15:41.565
I trust you.

15:41.649 --> 15:45.068
I didn't even have a chance
to become really good at sports.

15:45.862 --> 15:49.740
- You know, I wasn't bad.
- What about the obvious remedy?

15:49.824 --> 15:53.243
[ Sighs ] Reversing things.
Maybe getting a job at a newspaper.

15:54.579 --> 15:56.538
I don't write.
[ Chuckles ]

15:59.667 --> 16:02.336
But that didn't stop me
from sending my audition tapes...

16:02.420 --> 16:06.089
to the bigger stations
and the networks.

16:07.008 --> 16:08.800
Well, come on.

16:08.885 --> 16:13.013
It is your life.
Nobody is tying you to the fast track.

16:17.143 --> 16:18.852
Did you go to college?

16:20.563 --> 16:24.191
So, you're not well educated,
you have almost no experience...

16:24.275 --> 16:25.776
and you can't write.

16:25.860 --> 16:27.778
Yeah, and I'm -
[ Chuckles ]

16:27.862 --> 16:30.072
and I'm making a fortune.

16:36.162 --> 16:38.955
It's hard for me to advise you...

16:39.040 --> 16:42.417
since you personify something
that I truly think is dangerous.

16:44.087 --> 16:45.337
Uh-huh.

16:45.421 --> 16:47.798
I agree with you.
You're not qualified. So get qualified.

16:47.882 --> 16:49.883
You can insist on being better prepared.

16:49.967 --> 16:51.677
You don't have to just leave it with...

16:51.761 --> 16:55.555
"Uh, I don't write, I'm not schooled...

16:55.640 --> 16:59.643
I don't understand the news I'm reading,
but at least I'm upset about it, folks."

17:02.897 --> 17:04.064
Whoa.

17:04.147 --> 17:07.442
Just what do you want from me anyway,
permission to be a fake?

17:07.527 --> 17:09.069
Stop whining.

17:09.153 --> 17:11.445
[ Exhales ]
Do something about it.

17:16.118 --> 17:17.493
Oh.

17:20.415 --> 17:22.415
Well, you don't have to
start right now.

17:25.795 --> 17:28.255
I hated the way
you talked to me just now.

17:30.842 --> 17:32.676
And it wasn't just because
you were right.

17:36.639 --> 17:43.437
[ Sighs ]

17:44.397 --> 17:46.314
Oh, God.
[ Chuckles ]

17:46.399 --> 17:48.400
Oh, God.

17:48.484 --> 17:50.068
[ Whimpers ]

17:51.654 --> 17:53.155
[ Sighs ]
Oh, God.

17:58.619 --> 17:59.745
[ Groans ]

17:59.829 --> 18:03.582
No. No. No.
It wasn't just the speech.

18:03.666 --> 18:05.709
The same thing happened
with this guy.

18:05.793 --> 18:09.463
I have passed some line someplace.

18:09.547 --> 18:13.175
I am beginning to repel people
I'm trying to seduce.

18:13.259 --> 18:16.303
- He must've been great-looking, right?
- Why do you say that?

18:16.387 --> 18:19.473
Because nobody invites
a bad-looking idiot to their bedroom.

18:21.100 --> 18:24.186
- Okay, let's do me.
- Sure.

18:24.270 --> 18:26.021
I feel like I'm slipping.

18:26.105 --> 18:28.857
But do people who are actually slipping
feel that way...

18:28.941 --> 18:31.568
or is it always the really good people
who are moving up...

18:31.652 --> 18:35.906
who invariably think they're slipping
because their standards are so high?

18:36.657 --> 18:39.618
This conversation is not worthy of you.

18:39.702 --> 18:42.579
- I'd give anything if that were true.
- Good night.

18:42.663 --> 18:47.209
Wouldn't this be a great world if insecurity
and desperation made us more attractive?

18:47.293 --> 18:49.503
If needy were a turn-on?

18:49.587 --> 18:51.671
Call if you get weird.

18:51.756 --> 18:54.132
- Mmm?
- Take care, doll.

18:54.217 --> 18:55.717
I will.

19:02.099 --> 19:03.600
[ Phone Rings ]

19:05.228 --> 19:08.605
I was just thinking it was the shortest
phone conversation we ever had.

19:08.689 --> 19:12.818
[ Tom ] Um, I never told you
the reason I was telling you everything before.

19:12.902 --> 19:14.528
Hey.

19:16.113 --> 19:20.742
Those audition tapes I sent out - I've been hired
by your network for the Washington bureau.

19:20.827 --> 19:23.411
So I'll probably be seeing you at work.

19:23.496 --> 19:24.913
What?

19:25.998 --> 19:27.207
Sorry.

19:30.545 --> 19:33.672
They didn't hire Peter Stiller from The Times,
and he had a great audition tape.

19:33.756 --> 19:35.799
You wanna start going over
who they could've gotten?

19:35.883 --> 19:38.385
They can't take on people like this
for network news.

19:38.469 --> 19:41.805
For God's sake, what is going on?

20:03.286 --> 20:05.787
[ Chattering ]

20:11.794 --> 20:15.672
Okay. What about this?
Here's a tough ethical one.

20:15.756 --> 20:18.216
Would you tell a source that you love them...

20:18.301 --> 20:19.926
just to get some information?

20:20.011 --> 20:21.011
- Yes.
- Yes.

20:21.095 --> 20:22.721
- Me, too.
- Sure.

20:22.805 --> 20:25.473
- [ Man ] You bet.
- Jennifer didn't know there was an alternative.

20:25.558 --> 20:27.559
[ Laughing ]

20:28.644 --> 20:30.145
Here's a good one.

20:30.229 --> 20:33.023
They allow us to have cameras
at an execution in Florida.

20:33.107 --> 20:37.277
Do you broadcast tape of the guy in the chair
when they turn on the voltage?

20:37.361 --> 20:38.570
- Sure.
- Why not?

20:38.654 --> 20:40.906
- Absolutely.
- You bet.

20:40.990 --> 20:43.074
Nothing like wrestling
with a moral dilemma, is there?

20:43.159 --> 20:46.244
- [ Tape Rewinding ]
- Yeah. Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah. Speak to you later.

20:46.329 --> 20:49.915
Okay, Bobby. Go back to 9:45:46.
The sound bite in the alley.

20:49.999 --> 20:52.250
It starts,
"So why were you in Angola?"

20:52.335 --> 20:54.377
- You know, we could go all -
- Please, Bobby! We're pushing.

20:57.298 --> 20:58.965
[ Tape Rewinding ]

21:05.556 --> 21:08.266
- [ Reporter ] So why were you in Angola?
- Why were you in Angola?

21:08.351 --> 21:09.851
- Politics? Money?
- Money?

21:09.936 --> 21:11.770
What brings you up as a mercenary?

21:11.854 --> 21:15.607
Well, that's where the job's at, you know?
That's what I get paid to do.

21:15.691 --> 21:19.027
They said I should observe the -
They said it would be okay.

21:19.111 --> 21:21.780
We're working here!
You can stand over in the, uh, uh -

21:21.864 --> 21:24.115
- Play back the last line.
- Thanks.

21:24.200 --> 21:25.951
- Bobby -
- You said something about -

21:26.035 --> 21:27.911
[ Jane ]
Let me hear it.

21:27.995 --> 21:30.372
[ Tape Rewinding ]

21:30.498 --> 21:35.502
- Jane. Jane! We need it in 14 minutes.
We're putting it directly into the feed.
- [ Telephone Rings ]

21:35.586 --> 21:38.338
Jane Craig. Just a second.
Let me hear it.

21:38.422 --> 21:41.091
[ Reporter ]...have a different meaning.
What did you expect...

21:41.175 --> 21:43.635
- when you - when you came back this time?
- Here.

21:43.719 --> 21:46.137
- Thank you.
- It's a long time since I've seen my folks...

21:46.222 --> 21:49.099
but, uh, I'm not expecting
any big homecoming.

21:49.183 --> 21:51.309
Stop there.

21:52.019 --> 21:55.438
Doll, I want to shoot the Homecoming from
a Norman Rockwell book I have in the office.

21:55.523 --> 21:59.025
- You don't have enough time! Not a chance!
- I'll be right down. It's real tight.

21:59.110 --> 22:02.737
All right. I have to tell Ernie about this
because there isn't enough time!

22:02.822 --> 22:04.990
Yes, there is!

22:05.825 --> 22:08.118
I don't think she's gonna make it.
[ Laughing ]

22:10.287 --> 22:13.123
[ Man On Monitor ]
It was a surprise at the Soviet embassy in Beirut.

22:13.207 --> 22:15.000
- You want copy?
- Yes, doll. Fifteen seconds.

22:15.084 --> 22:16.376
- [ Kisses ]
- Ooh.

22:16.460 --> 22:18.795
Okay, Bobby. Just a two-second dissolve
to the Rockwell.

22:19.755 --> 22:22.340
- Now should I -
- Just a two-second dissolve!

22:27.930 --> 22:31.641
Jesus! We have three minutes!
Why do you do this to me?

22:31.726 --> 22:33.560
Is it because I won an award?

22:33.644 --> 22:37.564
Homecoming -
Norman Rockwell's enduring portrait.

22:37.648 --> 22:42.193
The return of a fighting man has always been
one of the more moving ceremonies of war.

22:42.278 --> 22:44.112
- [ Coughing ]
- We have a minute and a half.

22:44.196 --> 22:47.866
It's my responsibility to tell the control room
and New York that we won't be ready.

22:47.950 --> 22:49.868
- Uh-uh. We'll be ready.
- In 84 seconds?

22:49.952 --> 22:53.455
- Fifteen seconds. Oh, God!
- You're saying, "Oh, God"?

22:53.539 --> 22:56.458
- Lay it in, Bobby. Back it up.
- They're gonna go up and the screen will be black.

22:56.542 --> 22:58.710
And they're gonna go to black
because we're not there!

22:58.794 --> 23:00.754
What about careers, huh?

23:00.838 --> 23:02.338
- We're not gonna make it!
- Bobby.

23:02.423 --> 23:04.340
- Whoops.
- "Whoops"?

23:04.425 --> 23:05.884
- [ Gasping ]
- Bobby, Bobby, Bobby.

23:05.968 --> 23:07.761
- Blair.
- Oh, God!

23:07.845 --> 23:09.554
- Bobby, Bobby, Bobby, Bobby.
- Blair!

23:11.891 --> 23:14.976
- You got it!
- We'll make it, Blair!

23:15.061 --> 23:16.728
[ Blair Gasping ]

23:16.812 --> 23:19.355
- Go!
- [ Gasping ]

23:19.440 --> 23:21.816
Hey! Watch it there!

23:24.153 --> 23:25.070
Whoo!

23:25.154 --> 23:26.946
- [ Gasps ]
- Whoa!

23:27.031 --> 23:29.407
Open the damn door!
Thank you!

23:31.702 --> 23:32.702
- Hey!
- Wow.

23:37.374 --> 23:39.084
Ow!

23:45.341 --> 23:47.342
[ Man ]
Call New York. We won't be ready.

23:47.426 --> 23:49.928
- [ Woman ] No, there she is.
- [ Woman #2 ] Okay. Stand by.

23:50.012 --> 23:53.264
- Five, four, three, two, one.
- Here!

23:53.349 --> 23:55.058
- Here it comes.
- Take it!

23:55.142 --> 23:56.601
[ Anchor On Monitor ]
Aaron Altman was there.

23:56.685 --> 24:00.271
[ Aaron ] In other times with other purposes there
might be a band and bunting at the bus depot...

24:00.356 --> 24:03.233
- Guys?
- for J.D. Singer's arrival home.

24:03.317 --> 24:07.570
Homecoming -
Norman Rockwell's enduring portrait.

24:07.655 --> 24:12.242
The return of a fighting man has always been
one of the more moving ceremonies of war.

24:12.326 --> 24:16.788
Tearful women, proud men,
excited children.

24:16.872 --> 24:19.290
But J.D. Singer was right.

24:19.375 --> 24:22.585
His homecoming was no big deal.

24:22.670 --> 24:24.838
Aaron Altman, Lincoln, Nebraska.

24:26.549 --> 24:29.634
[ Anchor On Monitor ]
An American comes home.

24:29.718 --> 24:32.303
That's your news.
I'm Bill Rorish.

24:32.388 --> 24:34.472
Good evening.

24:34.557 --> 24:36.558
Look at that smile.

24:37.434 --> 24:39.102
That was good work.

24:39.186 --> 24:40.812
His, uh -

24:40.896 --> 24:43.690
- Hey, Bill smiled. He liked it.
- No, Bill loved it. That's a big smile.

24:43.774 --> 24:47.986
I haven't seen Bill
smile like that in weeks!

24:48.070 --> 24:50.613
- Good piece.
- Thanks, Ernie.

24:50.698 --> 24:52.615
I gotta see it again. Ernie?

24:57.913 --> 25:00.874
- He did smile.
- [ Chuckling ]

25:00.958 --> 25:03.877
- D-Don't tell anyone I did this.
- [ Chuckling ]

25:05.546 --> 25:07.964
- Oh -
- I'm sorry if I got in the way.

25:08.048 --> 25:10.008
It was - It was -
It was totally impressive!

25:10.092 --> 25:12.594
It was - It was just a great piece!

25:12.678 --> 25:14.554
You weren't. Thanks.

25:14.638 --> 25:17.015
- How does it feel being here?
- Oh, I can't believe I'm here.

25:17.099 --> 25:20.059
- Uh, do you know where Martin went?
- I think he went downstairs.

25:20.144 --> 25:22.353
- Okay, thanks.
- I can't believe I'm really here, you know?

25:22.438 --> 25:25.982
No, I'm wrong.
He went to Research.

25:26.066 --> 25:29.068
[ Chuckling ]
I can't believe I'm really here.

25:29.153 --> 25:31.863
-No kidding. If you're through work now, we could -
-No.

25:31.947 --> 25:36.159
Aaron and I go to Central America
on Wednesday, so I am cramming.

25:36.911 --> 25:39.204
I thought you were incredible in there.

25:40.206 --> 25:41.706
E-Everybody was.

25:42.541 --> 25:45.543
I know how much I have to learn.
If I could - I mean, i-i -

25:45.628 --> 25:47.670
I would really a lot appreciate it if -

25:47.755 --> 25:50.673
"Really a lot appreciate it"?

25:53.135 --> 25:54.636
You make me nervous.

25:57.389 --> 25:58.640
Anyway...

26:00.392 --> 26:01.893
if I can pick your brain -

26:01.977 --> 26:03.895
if -

26:06.815 --> 26:10.276
I-I can't help you. Sorry.
I'm not here to teach remedial reporting.

26:14.865 --> 26:19.702
And it has nothing to do with the fact
that I left your room instead of staying there?

26:25.668 --> 26:27.585
Oh!

26:30.631 --> 26:32.173
[ Scoffs ]

26:33.175 --> 26:34.634
Please.

26:40.266 --> 26:42.600
You're gonna have to
understand something.

26:42.685 --> 26:44.477
This isn't personal.

26:47.356 --> 26:48.356
Okay.

26:53.612 --> 26:55.363
- Good night.
- Good night.

26:58.284 --> 27:00.535
[ Speaking Spanish ]

27:05.874 --> 27:08.543
Okay, okay. Está bien. Está bien.

27:08.627 --> 27:11.337
- ¿Va a haber tiroteo?
- Sí.

27:11.422 --> 27:14.299
- ¿Qué tan malo puede ser?
- Malo.

27:14.383 --> 27:15.383
Gracias.

27:15.467 --> 27:16.634
Oye.

27:16.719 --> 27:19.804
Para un americano,
no hablas mal español.

27:19.888 --> 27:23.850
Really? Well, I'm sure
you speak English very well too. Thank you.

27:25.644 --> 27:29.480
Ready for this? He says they've been
engaging the Sandinistas regularly.

27:29.565 --> 27:32.608
He thinks there's gonna be shooting tonight.

27:32.693 --> 27:33.901
[ Chuckles ]

27:36.655 --> 27:37.947
Look at her.

27:38.032 --> 27:41.576
Hey. If anything happens to me,
you tell every woman I've ever gone out with...

27:41.660 --> 27:43.453
that I was talking about her at the end.

27:43.537 --> 27:45.330
That way they'll have to reevaluate me.

27:45.414 --> 27:47.915
[ Laughing ]

27:48.000 --> 27:50.335
[ Chattering In Spanish ]

27:50.419 --> 27:52.128
[ Speaking Spanish ]
Put on the boot.

27:52.212 --> 27:54.255
[ Jane ]
No! Manny, no!

27:54.340 --> 27:57.050
What the hell? No.
Stop, stop, stop, stop.

27:57.134 --> 27:59.677
We are not here to stage the news.
Wait and see what they do.

27:59.762 --> 28:02.013
Sir, you - you can do whatever you want.

28:04.683 --> 28:06.684
It's your choice.

28:16.695 --> 28:18.321
Okay.

28:21.492 --> 28:23.785
[ Man Whispering In Spanish ]

28:23.869 --> 28:26.412
[ Aaron Whispering ]
He just said he's scared.

28:30.918 --> 28:33.294
- [ Gunfire ]
- [ Shouting In Spanish ]

28:33.379 --> 28:35.380
- [ Jane ] Okay, let's get this.
- [ Manny ] Too dark!

28:35.464 --> 28:37.840
[ Jane ]
No, it's not too dark. Just go!

28:37.925 --> 28:39.801
- Aaron, go.
- [ Gunfire ]

28:45.015 --> 28:49.185
The first shots were fired not 1 0 seconds ago
from over there towards the east.

28:49.269 --> 28:51.479
- [ Gunfire Continues ]
- The contras -

28:51.563 --> 28:55.733
The contras feel they must be outnumbered.
This is so small a unit. That's a given.

28:55.818 --> 28:58.152
- Still, they've managed to hold their ground -
- [ Gunfire Continues ]

28:58.237 --> 29:00.696
despite the fact that their weapons
have been acting up...

29:00.781 --> 29:03.908
either misfiring or jamming.

29:03.992 --> 29:06.828
No new shipment of arms is expected
until tomorrow.

29:06.912 --> 29:09.497
All they got today... were the shoes.

29:10.833 --> 29:13.418
Great line at the end, man.
It could have been great. It was great.

29:13.502 --> 29:15.420
- Did you get a shot of the boots?
- Yeah. Of course.

29:15.504 --> 29:18.881
- So then we can cut back to that at the end.
- To the pan of the supply boxes.

29:18.966 --> 29:23.302
I can't believe I just risked my life for a network
that tests my face with focus groups!

29:25.180 --> 29:27.473
- I don't feel good.
- [ Laughs ]

29:28.642 --> 29:31.561
[ Sobbing ]

29:53.375 --> 29:56.002
- [ Man ] Stand by -
- The proposal calls for electing a president...

29:56.086 --> 29:57.962
from among several candidates.

29:58.046 --> 30:01.215
- [ Woman ] We got the graphic on in two seconds.
- Hi.

30:01.300 --> 30:02.884
How's it goin'?

30:03.886 --> 30:08.139
- [ Man ] C.C., we need control of five -
-...chosen by the military command.

30:08.223 --> 30:12.477
A firefight along the Nicaraguan border
when we return.

30:12.561 --> 30:15.646
- [ Gunfire On Monitor ]
- [ Man ] Audio is up full here.

30:15.731 --> 30:19.775
The first shots were fired not 10 seconds ago
from over there towards the east.

30:19.860 --> 30:23.070
[ Man ]
Freeze. Freeze it back over E.S.S.A.

30:23.155 --> 30:25.364
[ Ernie ]
Congratulations, you two.

30:25.449 --> 30:28.075
Finally got a piece in a few minutes early, huh?

30:28.160 --> 30:30.328
I hear Bill saw it this morning,
and he loved it.

30:30.412 --> 30:33.539
- [ Aaron ] No kidding?
- Yeah.

30:33.624 --> 30:35.416
[ Man ]
No one's checked the spelling on these Chyrons.

30:35.501 --> 30:39.170
There's a guy downstairs.
Clerk brought him in and vouched for him.

30:39.254 --> 30:43.216
He says he has something to say
about gays getting promotions at State.

30:44.092 --> 30:47.345
Maybe I could buy you dinner sometime soon.

30:47.429 --> 30:50.181
I-I just got back.
I don't know which end is up.

30:50.265 --> 30:51.599
Okay.

30:52.935 --> 30:56.521
Jane, Bill Rorish wants
to speak to you at the break.

30:56.605 --> 30:57.772
- Now.
- Wow.

30:57.856 --> 31:01.400
I've never heard of him handing out
compliments in the middle of a show.

31:03.070 --> 31:04.946
- Jane?
- Yes.

31:05.030 --> 31:09.534
Darling, if it gets any better than that, I'm going
to have to bring you up here to New York.

31:09.618 --> 31:12.495
Thanks. I - I just wish you'd kept
the first 20 seconds.

31:12.579 --> 31:14.956
- [ Groans ]
- But thank you.

31:15.040 --> 31:20.711
WeIl, the, uh, visual with
the shoes at the end was just perfect.

31:20.796 --> 31:22.713
God, he loved the boots!

31:22.798 --> 31:25.341
Aaron should be hearing this
so I can have an extra witness.

31:25.425 --> 31:29.679
WelI, you always want to give
the credit away, don't you?

31:30.472 --> 31:32.640
No, I don't.
He happens to deserve the credit.

31:32.724 --> 31:36.269
- He's right here.
- I’ll speak to you soon.

31:39.231 --> 31:41.566
He had to read over some new copy.

31:42.734 --> 31:43.734
Oh?

31:43.819 --> 31:46.946
♪♪ [ Humming ]

31:51.159 --> 31:52.743
- [ Clears Throat ]
- What?

31:55.872 --> 31:59.292
Is it okay if I watch you
tape that interview downstairs?

31:59.376 --> 32:01.002
- Yes.
- Thanks.

32:01.086 --> 32:05.923
The contras have only a few months -
[ Continues, Indistinct ]

32:06.008 --> 32:08.009
[ Whispering ]
Laugh so they don't think I'm dying inside...

32:08.093 --> 32:11.721
but have so much style
that I just said something funny.

32:12.514 --> 32:15.391
[ Laughing ]

32:15.475 --> 32:17.101
What'd he say?

32:18.854 --> 32:20.563
Oh, I'll never tell.

32:24.526 --> 32:27.320
A year and a half ago
I made some stupid remark about his hairline.

32:27.404 --> 32:29.363
He's never gonna forget it!
This way.

32:29.448 --> 32:31.741
[ Laughs ]

32:31.825 --> 32:34.368
Okay. I'll meet the crew there then.

32:35.162 --> 32:38.497
Right. Could you give me that address
one more time?

32:38.582 --> 32:39.832
Right.

32:40.626 --> 32:43.753
Yeah, it's good to finally
be getting to work.

32:45.380 --> 32:47.548
17204 Colorado.

32:47.633 --> 32:49.634
Right. Like the state. Yeah.

32:49.718 --> 32:52.261
17204.

32:52.346 --> 32:55.348
Got it. 1-7-2-0-4?

32:57.351 --> 32:58.851
Yeah. Bye.

32:59.895 --> 33:01.646
[ Sighs ]

33:03.190 --> 33:04.815
1-7-2-

33:04.900 --> 33:07.026
1-7-2-0-4.

33:07.819 --> 33:10.863
Jane? I've got a story.

33:10.947 --> 33:12.406
Jane?

33:19.414 --> 33:21.374
[ Horn Honking ]

33:23.335 --> 33:27.254
- [ Jane ] Hi. How are you?
- Wait. I need you.

33:32.302 --> 33:33.969
I got a story.

33:34.054 --> 33:37.515
Some public official skipped a week
on his Christmas club?

33:37.599 --> 33:40.059
The House Armed Services Committee
has a secret report...

33:40.143 --> 33:43.938
which says that the Allen fighting vehicle
the army poured a fortune into...

33:44.022 --> 33:45.523
plain won't work.

33:45.607 --> 33:48.359
- I've got it cold, confirmed.
- Hmm.

33:48.443 --> 33:51.737
- They have $5 million in this thing already.
- Billion.

33:52.906 --> 33:55.241
Right, billion. Okay. Of course.

33:55.325 --> 33:58.994
They said I could have any producer I want...

33:59.079 --> 34:00.871
and I want you.

34:00.956 --> 34:02.498
[ Mortar Fire On TV ]

34:02.582 --> 34:05.876
[ Tom ] One committee source referred to it
as a $5 billion metal sculpture...

34:05.961 --> 34:09.045
too ugly to look at and too big to bury.

34:09.130 --> 34:11.297
Over time, however,
costs have doubled...

34:11.382 --> 34:14.051
and the system has had serious problems.

34:14.136 --> 34:16.887
- Did you write this?
- I write for you sometimes.

34:16.972 --> 34:18.639
Not because you have to.

34:21.601 --> 34:24.061
- The suspension system had to be redesigned -
- [ Mocking Tom ]

34:24.146 --> 34:25.980
because of the vehicle’s extra weight.

34:26.063 --> 34:29.190
The addition of the TOW missile has meant
the Allen can carry only six infantrymen.

34:29.275 --> 34:33.446
- Oh, come on.
- The heavier armor has caused
the vehicle to sink in shallow water.

34:33.530 --> 34:36.197
General Elton McGuire is in charge
of the weapons system.

34:36.283 --> 34:38.743
- Have just a second? Please.
- No.

34:38.827 --> 34:41.911
General - General, I don't want
to bother you anymore.

34:43.123 --> 34:45.541
- Or your family.
- [ Aaron ] So Tom rates two cameras, huh?

34:45.625 --> 34:49.210
But tomorrow there's gonna be
a mob of me out here.

34:49.295 --> 34:52.965
So if you have anything to say, sir,
why not say it now the way you want.

34:53.049 --> 34:55.009
That's great. That's great.

34:55.092 --> 34:58.137
I think it's great you left in what you said.
Just great.

34:58.221 --> 35:02.391
Yes. Please, let's never forget,
we're the real story, not them.

35:03.059 --> 35:06.353
Yeah, I know.
I went back and forth on it.

35:06.438 --> 35:09.398
[ Blair ]
I liked it. He's not afraid of being human.

35:09.483 --> 35:10.941
- Shh!
- The general will appear tomorrow...

35:11.026 --> 35:13.778
before the House Armed Services Committee.

35:13.862 --> 35:17.198
- Tom Grunick, the Pentagon.
- And as if the pentagon...

35:17.282 --> 35:20.534
- didn't have enough problems,
tonight it announced...
- Thanks, Jane.

35:20.619 --> 35:22.703
- that its new Action Army helmet is defective.
- Sure.

35:22.788 --> 35:24.872
Tom?

35:24.956 --> 35:27.625
Um, my youngest wanted to meet you.

35:27.709 --> 35:29.418
- This is Elli.
- Hi, Elli.

35:29.503 --> 35:31.921
- Hi.
- You should be honored.

35:32.005 --> 35:34.548
- She never wanted to meet anyone here before.
- Dad.

35:34.633 --> 35:39.720
[ Chuckles ] But she said that
she just loved you on television just now.

35:41.306 --> 35:44.391
Hi, Elli. Remember me?

35:44.476 --> 35:46.769
I-I'm not sure. I'm - I'm sorry.

35:46.853 --> 35:48.437
I've been to your house.

35:48.522 --> 35:52.650
And Aaron was on that, uh,
14-day raft trip with us last year.

35:58.615 --> 36:02.326
- Oh, yeah.
- I had that big yellow raincoat on.

36:02.410 --> 36:03.994
- Oh, yeah.
- It had a hood.

36:04.079 --> 36:05.871
- Yeah. Hi!
- Yes.

36:05.956 --> 36:08.958
- It was over my head.
- Yeah. Your hair's different.

36:09.042 --> 36:10.501
- Yeah.
- Hi.

36:10.585 --> 36:13.462
Hi, Elli. She knows me.

36:14.548 --> 36:16.298
[ Tom ]
Hi, Dad.

36:17.342 --> 36:18.843
Did you see it?

36:20.804 --> 36:23.597
Great. I'll send you a tape.

36:25.433 --> 36:27.184
I'm sorry I haven't called.

36:27.269 --> 36:29.603
Things got a...

36:29.688 --> 36:31.730
little bumpy for a while.

36:32.482 --> 36:34.441
No, it's not important.
I'm fine.

36:36.069 --> 36:37.278
Hey, Dad?

36:39.197 --> 36:42.116
I think I just may be able
to do this job.

36:44.327 --> 36:46.120
[ Laughing ]

36:46.204 --> 36:48.622
Well, I'm - I'm glad you were sure.

36:51.501 --> 36:54.461
Ah. Our host.

36:54.546 --> 36:57.423
- Come on in.
- Sorry we're late. It's Jane's fault.

36:57.507 --> 36:59.008
- Watch your attitude.
- Smells good.

36:59.092 --> 37:00.926
It is good.
Anne's been working all weekend.

37:01.011 --> 37:03.721
I don't know why
we have to feel defensive about it.

37:03.805 --> 37:05.973
Newspapers are in business
to make money.

37:06.057 --> 37:07.600
Why not us?

37:07.684 --> 37:10.895
I mean, they criticize us
for supposedly pandering...

37:10.979 --> 37:13.814
while they run Wingo games.

37:13.899 --> 37:16.066
Exactly right.

37:16.151 --> 37:18.235
Excuse me.
I'm paid to mix.

37:18.320 --> 37:20.988
[ Chuckling ]
Good-bye, Paul.

37:21.072 --> 37:22.656
Take care, Paul.

37:24.784 --> 37:29.580
It takes a certain kind of courage to talk like that
in front of the president of the news division.

37:29.664 --> 37:33.000
You think anyone who's proud
of the work we do is an ass-kisser.

37:33.084 --> 37:36.420
No. I think anyone
who puckers up their lips...

37:36.504 --> 37:40.966
and presses it against their boss's buttocks
and then smooches is an ass-kisser.

37:42.510 --> 37:44.386
My gosh.

37:44.471 --> 37:48.933
For a while there,
I was attracted to you.

37:49.017 --> 37:51.518
Well, wait a minute.
That changes everything.

37:53.104 --> 37:56.273
[ Man ] So they wouldn't renew
my magazine subscription because of money.

37:56.358 --> 37:59.026
- [ Jane ] I can't believe it.
- [ Man Laughing ]

37:59.110 --> 38:02.780
- It's happening all -
- Martin, would you excuse us for a minute?

38:02.864 --> 38:05.532
- No.
- Ah, go away.

38:11.039 --> 38:14.208
Well, you know,
I've been meaning to ask you -

38:16.211 --> 38:18.921
Ah, forget it.

38:20.048 --> 38:21.548
This is very awkward.

38:26.972 --> 38:30.933
[ Sighs ]
I see Tom around you a lot.

38:31.017 --> 38:34.103
And it's such a small office,
and I'd like to see him outside of work.

38:34.187 --> 38:37.815
Unless there's some reason for you to mind,
in which case I just won't do anything.

38:37.899 --> 38:41.735
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Do I mind? Why would I mind? No.

38:42.988 --> 38:44.279
Wait.

38:50.704 --> 38:52.246
I do mind.

38:55.583 --> 38:57.584
I mean, I think about him
outside of work sometimes...

38:57.669 --> 39:00.504
but I know I don't respect him.

39:03.591 --> 39:07.011
So what am I talking about?
What am I saying to you?

39:07.095 --> 39:10.305
You're saying stay away from him.

39:10.390 --> 39:13.976
- I can't be.
- We don't have to settle this definitively right now.

39:14.769 --> 39:16.270
Wait a minute. Wait a minute!

39:17.564 --> 39:20.065
♪♪ [ Piano ]

39:24.320 --> 39:26.447
[ Tom Laughing ]

39:30.076 --> 39:32.244
- Wanna sing something?
- Slippery.

39:35.248 --> 39:36.707
I will call you.

39:36.791 --> 39:39.001
I'll go in the other room right now and call you.

39:39.085 --> 39:40.878
[ Man ]
I've made a study of these things.

39:40.962 --> 39:45.132
Tell me one person who ever left television news
to work on a newspaper.

39:45.216 --> 39:47.134
You're right.

39:47.218 --> 39:49.344
It sure looks good.

39:49.429 --> 39:52.723
- [ Clatters ]
- [ Chattering ]

39:54.517 --> 39:57.394
[ Woman ]
After all these years, we have a life.

39:57.479 --> 39:58.979
- See you.
- Sure. See you.

40:05.153 --> 40:06.487
Hey.

40:07.489 --> 40:09.114
- Hi, Tom.
- Hi.

40:09.199 --> 40:10.783
Hi.

40:10.867 --> 40:13.077
It's the first time
I've seen you dressed like this.

40:14.579 --> 40:16.580
You look so clean and pretty.

40:17.499 --> 40:19.833
What do you mean? Clean?

40:19.918 --> 40:24.046
[ Chuckles ] Well, at the office
you always have this sort of film over you.

40:27.300 --> 40:29.635
- I've got to find someone.
- [ Chuckles ]

40:29.719 --> 40:32.513
It's important.
Excuse me.

40:42.023 --> 40:44.108
[ Jane ]
Jennifer.

40:44.192 --> 40:46.568
Hey. Jennifer!

40:47.529 --> 40:50.322
Forget what I said.
You do whatever you want to with Tom.

40:50.406 --> 40:53.659
[ Scoffs ]
There's nothing I'm gonna do right this second.

40:53.743 --> 40:56.703
Oh, come on.
It's your day off.

40:57.455 --> 40:59.414
You're entitled.

41:03.711 --> 41:05.629
[ Chattering ]

41:05.713 --> 41:08.006
[ Phone Ringing ]

41:11.719 --> 41:14.263
- [ Ringing Continues ]
- [ Tom ] Hi.

41:18.726 --> 41:21.812
A plane just shot up
one of our bases in ltaly.

41:21.896 --> 41:25.482
- Casualties?
- Uh - This could be very, very -

41:25.567 --> 41:27.151
That's it!

41:29.154 --> 41:30.654
Okay, right away.

41:34.993 --> 41:36.160
Ernie?

41:36.244 --> 41:38.996
Tom? Tom.

41:39.080 --> 41:40.956
- Yeah.
- [ Blair ] What is it?

41:41.040 --> 41:43.417
A Libyan plane just shot up
one of our bases in Sicily.

41:43.501 --> 41:45.878
This might be a good time
to tap that source of ours.

41:45.962 --> 41:49.006
You might have an angle or something.
Jennifer, we need you.

41:56.014 --> 41:59.391
Jane, we want you to exec produce
a special report.

42:00.768 --> 42:03.687
- What?
- A Libyan plane just shot up
one of our bases in Sicily.

42:03.771 --> 42:05.480
It's all still happening.

42:05.565 --> 42:08.275
Since Paul is here,
he's made out the assignments -

42:08.359 --> 42:12.237
Uh, Jennifer at the White House.
George at the Pentagon. Martin at State.

42:12.322 --> 42:15.991
And we're gonna need an anchor,
since Rorish is on his boat.

42:16.075 --> 42:19.453
So we're gonna do the whole report
this afternoon from here with Tom.

42:19.537 --> 42:21.038
What?

42:22.957 --> 42:24.666
[ Chuckles ]

42:24.751 --> 42:27.169
- You're - You're not gonna use him at all?
- It's not my choice.

42:29.005 --> 42:32.424
- It's 1:35, and it's Tom.
- [ Chattering ]

42:32.508 --> 42:35.135
Um, you can reach me at the office.

42:35.220 --> 42:39.056
Paul, forgive me. I'm really sorry.
Pardon me for interrupting, but -

42:39.140 --> 42:42.476
Paul, uh, yes, I need to talk to you outside
for just a minute.

42:43.811 --> 42:44.978
Great.

42:51.986 --> 42:55.072
Tom's not ready for the job
you're about to hand him. Not near ready.

42:55.156 --> 42:56.990
Not by the longest shot.

42:57.075 --> 43:00.244
Now, Aaron spent six weeks in Tripoli.
He's interviewed Qaddafi.

43:00.328 --> 43:02.246
He reported on the '81 story.

43:02.330 --> 43:05.123
I think he's essential to do the job
we're capable of.

43:05.208 --> 43:08.418
And I think it's my responsibility
to tell you that.

43:08.503 --> 43:11.088
Okay, that's your opinion.
I don't agree.

43:11.172 --> 43:12.589
It's not opinion.

43:14.676 --> 43:17.761
You're just absolutely right...

43:17.845 --> 43:19.429
and I'm absolutely wrong.

43:21.849 --> 43:25.727
It must be nice to always
believe you know better...

43:25.812 --> 43:28.647
to always think you're
the smartest person in the room.

43:29.691 --> 43:31.400
No, it's awful.

43:33.111 --> 43:35.279
You better get going.

43:39.367 --> 43:40.867
[ Door Closes ]

43:42.203 --> 43:45.289
- Hey, Ed!
- [ Chattering ]

43:45.373 --> 43:47.416
[ Tires Screech ]

43:47.500 --> 43:48.959
[ Woman ]
Would you come on?

43:49.043 --> 43:51.211
- Nervous?
- Excited.

43:53.381 --> 43:56.008
Tell George and Jennifer
to try and cover everything...

43:56.092 --> 43:58.760
without Tom having to ask
additional questions.

43:58.845 --> 44:02.139
- Okay, Bobby says we gotta -
- Did you hear what I just said?

44:02.223 --> 44:04.308
Do you have that?
Take a breath.

44:04.392 --> 44:07.144
[ Inhales, Exhales ]
Hmm.

44:07.228 --> 44:10.022
And the most important thing -

44:10.106 --> 44:11.606
make sure his earpiece works.

44:11.691 --> 44:14.192
Have backups ready.
That's never been more vital.

44:14.277 --> 44:17.154
He must be able to hear me
at every second, and clearly.

44:17.238 --> 44:20.407
- [ Phone Ringing ]
- [ Chattering ]

44:35.548 --> 44:37.799
[ Man ]
Can someone get a picture of E-2C Hawkeyes...

44:37.884 --> 44:40.177
so I can do it on the paint box?

44:40.261 --> 44:43.180
[ Phone Ringing ]

44:43.264 --> 44:46.266
[ Blowing Through Lips ]

44:51.564 --> 44:53.565
We're going to the White House.

44:54.609 --> 44:55.776
Tom.

44:58.571 --> 45:01.073
- We have 20 minutes.
- [ Woman ] Shit!

45:01.157 --> 45:04.743
- You can wait in the studio.
- [ Man ] I got Tom's copy.

45:06.454 --> 45:08.288
[ Clears Throat ]

45:15.046 --> 45:18.131
♪♪ [ Acoustic Guitar Intro ]

45:23.054 --> 45:25.055
♪♪ [ Man Singing In French ]

45:27.475 --> 45:30.102
♪♪ [ Singing Along In French ]

45:50.623 --> 45:51.623
[ Groans ]

45:52.792 --> 45:55.252
- Stand by animation.
- [ Chattering ]

45:55.336 --> 45:56.503
Ready V.T.R. one and two.

45:56.587 --> 45:58.422
Ready to announce.

45:58.506 --> 46:01.925
- Ready on camera one with cue.
- Roll some three-quarter inch. Okay. Stand by.

46:02.009 --> 46:04.761
- Good luck, Jane.
- Ready.

46:11.644 --> 46:13.603
- All right. I need five.
- Six.

46:13.688 --> 46:17.232
- All right. And stand by, please.
- Thirty seconds to air time. Ready.

46:17.316 --> 46:19.651
All the remotes checked in?
Everyone here is programmed clearly?

46:19.735 --> 46:21.027
- Got it.
- Yeah, everyone's good.

46:21.112 --> 46:24.781
Executive producer. Wow!

46:24.866 --> 46:26.533
- Stand by V.T. five.
- [ Gagging ]

46:26.617 --> 46:28.452
- How many seconds to air?
- Thirty seconds.

46:28.536 --> 46:30.787
- All right. Stand by camera one, please.
- ♪♪ [ News Theme ]

46:30.872 --> 46:33.290
Camera two, center it up.
Just a little bit to the left.

46:33.374 --> 46:36.960
- Tom, can you hear me?
- Ready V.T. one and two?

46:37.044 --> 46:39.796
Tom, can you hear me? Tom?

46:39.881 --> 46:41.131
Tom? Tom?

46:41.215 --> 46:43.383
Tom! Tom!

46:43.468 --> 46:47.387
Damn it! He can't hear me!
I told you, if there was one thing -

46:47.472 --> 46:50.557
I can hear you. I was just teasing.
[ Chuckles ]

46:50.641 --> 46:53.894
- On five, four, three -
- Stand by.

46:53.978 --> 46:56.313
- And announce.
- Two, one -

46:56.397 --> 46:59.316
- And cue him with effects.
- A special report with Tom Grunick.

46:59.400 --> 47:02.527
Good afternoon.
A Libyan fighter plane attacked...

47:02.612 --> 47:08.658
a United States military installation
at Comiso, Sicily, at 10:07 a.m., eastern time.

47:08.743 --> 47:13.038
The Libyan MiG-21 was itself shot down
by American F-14 jets.

47:13.122 --> 47:18.126
- Oh.
- The base, a U.S. naval air station
on the island of Sicily.

47:18.211 --> 47:20.795
There are some 500 men and women
stationed there.

47:20.880 --> 47:25.342
The Libyan bombs destroyed a navy warehouse
which just 30 minutes earlier...

47:25.426 --> 47:26.927
had been crowded with servicemen.

47:27.011 --> 47:28.345
[ With Stereo ]
♪ Ooh, ooh ♪

47:28.429 --> 47:30.847
- ♪ Bought a one-way ticket back ♪
- ♪ Ticket back ♪

47:30.932 --> 47:33.725
- ♪ One-way ticket back ♪
- ♪ To the life ♪

47:33.809 --> 47:36.269
♪ I can sing while I read ♪

47:36.354 --> 47:40.023
♪ I am singing and reading both ♪

47:40.107 --> 47:41.775
♪ Leavin' ♪

47:41.859 --> 47:44.611
♪ On that midnight train to Georgia ♪

47:44.695 --> 47:47.030
♪ Leavin' on that midnight train ♪

47:47.114 --> 47:50.075
[ Man ]
The Libyan MiG-21 dropped all four of its bombs...

47:50.159 --> 47:53.245
on the U.S. air station in Comiso, Sicily.

47:53.329 --> 47:57.207
[ Tom ] The heat-seeking missiles
virtually disintegrated the plane on contact.

47:57.291 --> 47:58.792
[ TV Clicks Off ]

47:59.377 --> 48:02.295
♪ I'd rather live in his world ♪

48:02.380 --> 48:03.880
♪ Than live without him ♪♪

48:03.965 --> 48:06.841
- [ Man ] Insert on V.T. five -
- All remotes, stand by, please.

48:06.926 --> 48:10.345
- [ Sneezes, Blows Nose ]
- [ Overlapping Chatter ]

48:11.305 --> 48:14.349
- George, you ready?
- Yeah. Should I cover everything...

48:14.433 --> 48:16.560
or shouId I say something
for Tom to ask me about?

48:16.644 --> 48:18.311
Cover everything.

48:19.313 --> 48:20.772
Okay. We're going to George.

48:20.856 --> 48:23.233
Say, "The Joint Chiefs are meeting.

48:23.317 --> 48:24.776
We have George Weln at the Pentagon."

48:24.860 --> 48:28.321
...flew back to the White House, according
to his aides, to better monitor the situation.

48:28.406 --> 48:30.031
George Weln is at the Pentagon...

48:30.116 --> 48:34.494
and reports that the attack,
presumably by a lone Libyan pilot...

48:34.579 --> 48:37.831
has resulted in a massive movement
of U.S. military might.

48:37.915 --> 48:42.544
A lot of alliteration from anxious anchors
placed in powerful posts!

48:42.628 --> 48:46.381
[ George On TV ]...attack on the U.S. base
was the work of a single Libyan pilot...

48:46.465 --> 48:50.927
or if the pilot was acting on instructions
from Libyan leader, Mu'ammar Qaddafi.

48:51.012 --> 48:53.138
- [ Woman ] New copy coming in.
- We now have Qaddafi on the screen.

48:53.222 --> 48:55.682
- We have effects.
- Qaddafi's Chyron is ready.

48:55.766 --> 48:58.393
- It's Aaron.
- [ Man ] You look a little soft on two.

48:58.477 --> 49:00.103
- Yes?
- Hi.

49:00.187 --> 49:03.898
Listen. The pilot that shot down
the Libyan in 1981 is stationed right here.

49:03.983 --> 49:05.442
Maybe you can get him.

49:05.526 --> 49:09.029
Also, Tom should say that the F-14
is one of the hardest planes to fly...

49:09.113 --> 49:10.614
and they're nicknamed "Tomcats."

49:10.698 --> 49:14.868
- Thank you.
- [ George ] Said Qaddafi, "This is not war."

49:14.952 --> 49:19.039
The F-14 is one of the most difficult planes
to master. They're called Tomcats.

49:19.123 --> 49:21.708
George, isn't the F-14 Tomcat...

49:21.792 --> 49:24.628
one of the most difficult machines
for a pilot to master?

49:24.712 --> 49:28.548
- I think you're right.
- In the '70s, the first crop had a number of crashes.

49:28.633 --> 49:31.801
There was trouble with them
in the early days back in the '70s.

49:31.886 --> 49:34.971
Thank you, George.
Jennifer Mack is standing by at the White House -

49:35.056 --> 49:38.266
I say it here, it comes out there.

49:38.351 --> 49:40.727
- Jennifer?
- [ Jennifer ] The White House is preparing...

49:40.811 --> 49:42.812
- a list of contingency plans.
- Six. All right. And stand by, please.

49:42.897 --> 49:44.773
- [ Phone Rings ]
- Hi.

49:44.857 --> 49:46.650
- Me again.
- Hi.

49:46.734 --> 49:48.860
Listen, Qaddafi doesn't
foam at the mouth or anything.

49:48.944 --> 49:50.904
When you speak to him, he, uh -

49:50.988 --> 49:52.530
he seems not at all nuts.

49:52.615 --> 49:56.701
Uh, he seems like a leader.
Very impressive self control. That's what's so crazy.

49:56.786 --> 50:00.955
Okay, good. And we have the '81 pilot
on the way in. Nobody else will have him.

50:01.040 --> 50:02.207
You're welcome.

50:02.291 --> 50:05.085
- So how does it feel to be executive producer?
- I gotta go.

50:05.169 --> 50:07.295
Me too. Gotta go.
Very busy here. Gotta go.

50:07.380 --> 50:09.089
- [ Phone Slams ]
- We're very busy.

50:10.591 --> 50:13.176
[ Man ]
Okay, stand by, camera one. Center up.

50:13.260 --> 50:15.845
We're going to remote three.

50:16.889 --> 50:19.599
It's the Gulf of Sidra.

50:19.684 --> 50:22.686
The name of the U.S. commander
is Nathan Benchley.

50:22.770 --> 50:24.521
In the summer of 1981...

50:24.605 --> 50:28.108
two Libyan jets suddenly attacked
two American F-14s -

50:28.192 --> 50:31.069
[ Jane In Earpiece ]
The plane they got in '81 was an Su-22.

50:31.153 --> 50:33.530
Today they got a MiG-21,
which is a better plane.

50:33.614 --> 50:36.324
-...that the gulf is part of Libya's territorial waters -
- You're doing really well.

50:36.409 --> 50:39.077
a view not shared by other nations,
including the U.S.

50:39.161 --> 50:43.707
After a brief dogfight, both Libyan jets
were downed by the American fighters.

50:43.833 --> 50:47.752
- The name is Nathan Benchley.
- The commander of one of those planes,
Nathan Benchley, is at the Pentagon.

50:47.837 --> 50:50.714
- So, Commander, it must have been tougher...
- That's great. That's great.

50:50.798 --> 50:52.716
today shooting down the MiG-21.

50:52.800 --> 50:54.634
The one you got was an Su-22.

50:54.719 --> 50:56.886
[ Jane On Earpiece ]
What's it like at the moment of confrontation?

50:56.971 --> 51:00.890
- What's it like to be in a real dogfight?
- Okay. After this guy we’ll go for a wrap-up.

51:00.975 --> 51:05.478
You’ll have about 10 seconds.
Ask him how does he know when he has a hit.

51:05.563 --> 51:09.524
Do you know you have a hit
from one of those screens inside your cockpit...

51:09.608 --> 51:12.152
- or can you actually see your missiles strike...
- That's good. That's good.

51:12.236 --> 51:14.070
- the other plane with your eye?
- That's good.

51:14.155 --> 51:15.613
[ Benchley ]
The equipment is very sophisticated...

51:15.698 --> 51:19.367
but, uh, from a pilot's point of view,
you Iike to see it to confirm it.

51:19.452 --> 51:21.244
Thank you, Commander.

51:21.328 --> 51:23.496
It has always been considered
an outlaw nation...

51:23.581 --> 51:26.583
but, strangely, some of those
who have interviewed Qaddafi...

51:26.667 --> 51:31.004
find him, in a phrase we like to use in this country,
very presidential.

51:31.088 --> 51:33.923
- Nice, Jane.
- Jane Craig. Just a minute.

51:34.008 --> 51:36.384
Then we're gonna go to Martin Klein at State
for the message from Libya.

51:36.469 --> 51:39.095
Then you're gonna have the carrier pilot
from the Sidra -

51:39.180 --> 51:40.680
What!

51:40.765 --> 51:43.266
No! You missed him?
We only have 10 minutes left!

51:43.350 --> 51:45.518
How can you talk to me
about parking problems?

51:45.603 --> 51:48.354
- Shh!
- No! Not you'll try! You'll do it!

51:48.439 --> 51:52.275
Do it! Or I'll fry your fat ass, Estelle!
Good-bye!

51:52.359 --> 51:55.320
- [ Slams Phone ]
- I had no idea she was this good.

51:55.404 --> 51:58.364
Tom. Tom.

51:59.909 --> 52:01.743
Fill for a second.

52:01.827 --> 52:04.037
- Tom?
- Go.

52:05.372 --> 52:07.957
The latest message seems to indicate...

52:08.042 --> 52:10.585
that the Libyan pilot
was acting on his own...

52:10.669 --> 52:13.463
- without authority from anyone else.
- Stand by, camera two.

52:13.547 --> 52:16.299
In other words, I think we're all okay.

52:16.383 --> 52:18.843
- [ Jane ] Okay, Tom, wrap it up.
- Who the hell cares what you think?

52:18.928 --> 52:22.847
The Libyan government has disavowed
any prior knowledge of the attack.

52:22.932 --> 52:25.642
I'm Tom Grunick reporting from Washington.

52:25.726 --> 52:27.227
Good afternoon.

52:27.311 --> 52:29.229
[ Man ]
Animation.

52:29.313 --> 52:32.607
- Thanks, everybody.
- [ Man ] We are out.

52:32.733 --> 52:36.945
- Nice job, Tom.
- [ Jane On P.A. ]
Everybody on the floor, thank you so much.

52:37.029 --> 52:38.822
Good job, buddy.

52:42.493 --> 52:46.371
Thanks. Hey, man, you're great.

52:46.455 --> 52:51.125
- [ Paul ] Never so proud of one of my decisions.
- [ Chattering ]

52:53.921 --> 52:56.089
Jane, great work.
Really, you know?

52:56.173 --> 52:58.216
- Really.
- Well, there were no major gaffes anyway.

52:58.300 --> 53:00.009
Oh!
[ Scoffs ]

53:00.094 --> 53:02.470
"No major gaffes."
[ Chuckling ]

53:02.555 --> 53:04.180
You were brilliant!

53:06.392 --> 53:08.810
- Josh, great stuff.
- Thank you.

53:08.894 --> 53:12.814
- Congratulations, Jane.
- You guys are so good. You guys!

53:12.898 --> 53:15.108
- Thank you, Jane.
- Thanks, Jane.

53:15.192 --> 53:16.693
- Thanks, Ernie.
- Sure.

53:16.777 --> 53:17.861
[ Sighs ]

53:17.945 --> 53:19.946
You know,
this was important for Tom.

53:20.072 --> 53:25.159
- There's that bonding thing that happens
between the public and an anchorman.
- I've gotta watch Paul address the troops.

53:25.244 --> 53:27.287
It's not the conventions anymore.

53:27.371 --> 53:29.706
It's this kind of moment.

53:29.790 --> 53:31.207
- Oh, hi.
- Hi.

53:31.292 --> 53:32.625
Wow!

53:32.710 --> 53:36.629
- Hey, Mr. Iceman! You were great.
- You too.

53:36.714 --> 53:38.840
- Great job there.
- Yeah, you too.

53:44.138 --> 53:45.889
- Good work, Tom.
- Thanks.

53:45.973 --> 53:46.973
[ Scoffs ]

53:47.057 --> 53:49.767
What a baptism, Tom! Congratulations.

53:49.852 --> 53:52.896
Thank you.
With all the help you get, it's easier than local.

53:52.980 --> 53:55.440
- Where's Jane? I'm still juiced.
- Uh, she's back there.

53:55.524 --> 53:56.816
Thanks.

53:56.901 --> 53:59.819
- Can I help you gentlemen?
- We're here to play the new news theme.

54:06.118 --> 54:08.202
- You're an amazing woman.
- [ Gasps ]

54:09.038 --> 54:11.748
What a feeling,
having you inside my head!

54:11.832 --> 54:15.752
Yeah. It was...
an unusual place to be.

54:15.836 --> 54:17.503
It's, like, indescribable.

54:17.588 --> 54:21.215
You knew just when
to feed me the next line.

54:22.426 --> 54:25.178
You knew the m - second
before I needed it.

54:25.262 --> 54:27.180
There was like a rhythm we got into.

54:27.264 --> 54:30.600
- It was like great sex!
- [ Gasps ]

54:30.684 --> 54:32.185
[ Laughing ]

54:32.269 --> 54:34.270
- You have to celebrate with me.
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.

54:34.355 --> 54:38.733
Everybody's going to the bar down the street.
What's it called? Cap's?

54:38.817 --> 54:40.777
I'm going over to Aaron's.

54:40.861 --> 54:42.862
But maybe I'll hook up
with all of you later.

